Citation.sTitle: Density and Heat Capacity as a Function of Temperature for Binary Mixtures of 1-Butyl-3-methylpyridinium Tetrafluoroborate + Water, + Ethanol, and + Nitromethane
Citation.sAbstract: Experimental measurements of density and isobaric molar heat capacity for the binary systems containing ionic liquid 1-butyl-3-methylpyridinium tetrafluoroborate + water, + ethanol, and + nitromethane are presented within the temperature range (293.15 to 318.15) K at atmospheric pressure. From these data, excess molar volumes and excess molar isobaric heat capacity are calculated and discussed based on arguments often used for the study of liquid mixtures.
